// logical operators

are used to perform logcal operations on data

op1 && op2      logical and    (binary)   
op1 || op2      logical or     (binary)
!op             logical not    (unary)

these operators can not modify the operand

these operators result will be  zero or one.

in logical and if first operand is zero (0)
then it will not check second operand 

in logical or if first operand is non zero 
then it will not check second operand








